========================================================
Round Robin
========================================================
Preemptive. Each ready process gets at most quantum=3 time units per turn. Arrivals at a time-slice boundary are queued before the preempted process.

Execution timeline:
  [ 0,  3)  P1
  [ 3,  6)  P2
  [ 6,  9)  P3
  [ 9, 12)  P4
  [12, 14)  P1
  [14, 17)  P4
  [17, 18)  P4

Compact Gantt view:
  |0 P1 |3 P2 |6 P3 |9 P4 |12 P1 |14 P4 |17 P4 |18

Per-process results:
Process        Arr   Burst    Prio  Deadline  FirstStart    Finish   Waiting  Turnaround  Response   Missed
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
P1               0       5       2        20           0        14         9          14         0       no
P2               0       3       1        20           3         6         3           6         3       no
P3               0       3       1        20           6         9         6           9         6       no
P4               0       7       3        20           9        18        11          18         9       no

Summary metrics:
  Makespan              : 18
  Total busy time       : 18
  CPU utilization       : 100.00%
  Throughput            : 0.22 processes/unit-time
  Average waiting time  : 7.25
  Average turnaround    : 11.75
  Average response time : 4.50
  Deadline misses       : 0 / 4


==================== POLICY COMPARISON ====================
Policy                              Avg Wait  Avg Turnaround      Avg Resp    Misses      Util %
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
FCFS - First Come First Served          6.00           10.50          6.00         0      100.00
SJF - Shortest Job First                5.00            9.50          5.00         0      100.00
Priority Scheduling                     5.00            9.50          5.00         0      100.00
Round Robin                             7.25           11.75          4.50         0      100.00

Interpretation hints:
  - Lower waiting/turnaround time is usually better for batch-style workloads.
  - Lower response time is important for interactive workloads.
  - Round Robin often improves response time, but can increase turnaround time.
  - Deadline misses show whether a policy is suitable for time-bound workloads.
